1
00:00:00,125 --> 00:00:04,042
This building was housing for the church guards

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:07,209
And the administration for the priest and clergy

3
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:10,918
There were also rooms here by the corner

4
00:00:11,209 --> 00:00:14,834
They were for orphans, given to them by the priests

5
00:00:15,375 --> 00:00:18,250
They made sure the children lacked nothing in these rooms

6
00:00:18,792 --> 00:00:21,918
This was a place for one family, sometimes three or four families

7
00:00:22,417 --> 00:00:25,000
Here is the hall, and these are the rooms

8
00:00:25,375 --> 00:00:27,584
About three families lived in them

9
00:00:28,292 --> 00:00:32,459
The priests would house poor Christian families here

10
00:00:32,876 --> 00:00:34,375
They brought them into the churches

11
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,834
To serve the house of God

12
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:39,792
And they also had

13
00:00:40,292 --> 00:00:41,709
This church

14
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:46,000
And these rooms, plus the toilet and showers

15
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:49,918
One room, two rooms, then a third and a fourth

16
00:00:49,959 --> 00:00:52,042
With an annex on the roof, a storage space upstairs

17
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,000
And here was another hall

18
00:00:54,500 --> 00:01:00,042
For the guard, his name was Abu Janet

19
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:02,250
He was originally from Lebanon

20
00:01:02,709 --> 00:01:05,667
He lived in this church and served it

21
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:07,459
They used to call him Abu Janet

22
00:01:08,042 --> 00:01:10,417
This was his place and his home

23
00:01:10,417 --> 00:01:14,500
And this other place was the residence and office of the priests

24
00:01:15,459 --> 00:01:17,959
The most famous resident of this church

25
00:01:18,334 --> 00:01:20,375
Was the priest they called <i>abouna</i> [our father]

26
00:01:20,417 --> 00:01:24,500
This was his main residence, with two rooms and an annex

27
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,959
With a bathroom and toilet, reserved for the priest

28
00:01:28,334 --> 00:01:31,083
The one they called <i>abouna</i>, servant of the church

29
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,626
Interviewer: Ahmad, you pointed to these rooms

30
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:36,167
Do you know what was inside them?

31
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:39,083
Witness: Rooms where they slept

32
00:01:39,125 --> 00:01:40,667
A room for sitting

33
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:42,209
And a dining room

34
00:01:42,459 --> 00:01:46,292
Sometimes used for rituals during holidays

35
00:01:46,751 --> 00:01:48,751
The household would receive

36
00:01:48,792 --> 00:01:52,751
Visitors from other churches

37
00:01:53,375 --> 00:01:55,250
They would welcome them

38
00:01:55,584 --> 00:01:58,792
Guests came and were given gifts for the holiday

39
00:01:58,959 --> 00:02:00,542
Yes, they gave out gifts

40
00:02:00,667 --> 00:02:03,542
They helped one another

41
00:02:04,709 --> 00:02:06,834
This room was for sitting

42
00:02:07,334 --> 00:02:08,667
That one for sleeping

43
00:02:09,083 --> 00:02:12,834
And this larger room was like a guest room

44
00:02:13,209 --> 00:02:15,417
When there was a meeting of priests

45
00:02:15,834 --> 00:02:18,250
A large hall, not for the guard

46
00:02:18,709 --> 00:02:22,626
If you can see it from here, you can film it

47
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:28,584
It was like a guest room, for meetings of priests

48
00:02:28,876 --> 00:02:30,584
Like the gatherings they held

49
00:02:30,959 --> 00:02:32,083
It was a big hall

50
00:02:33,792 --> 00:02:36,959
These were the houses of guards serving the church

51
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:40,626
And this was their conference hall

52
00:02:41,459 --> 00:02:45,792
They called it the hall, it had a full set of couches

53
00:02:46,584 --> 00:02:49,667
During meetings, priests came and sat here

54
00:02:49,709 --> 00:02:51,709
This was the corridor

55
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:55,959
And these windows, this was a big hall

56
00:02:56,375 --> 00:02:59,751
Their council hall for priestly meetings

57
00:03:00,417 --> 00:03:03,459
And this wall

58
00:03:05,834 --> 00:03:09,709
Beyond it were churches, called Housh al-Biaa

59
00:03:10,209 --> 00:03:11,834
Which was made up of five churches

60
00:03:12,334 --> 00:03:15,167
This was the conference hall for priests and the church

61
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:18,042
Interviewer: What was here exactly?
Witness: There were rows of chairs

62
00:03:18,209 --> 00:03:21,292
Like an office, this was the church’s administration

63
00:03:21,584 --> 00:03:24,834
There were rows of chairs here and there

64
00:03:25,417 --> 00:03:26,792
And another row here

65
00:03:27,584 --> 00:03:31,292
A desk here, like a director’s desk

66
00:03:31,667 --> 00:03:33,918
A desk with a swivel chair

67
00:03:34,417 --> 00:03:39,125
He sat here, this was the church administration office

68
00:03:40,167 --> 00:03:44,000
Chairs placed here and there, priests gathered for meetings

69
00:03:44,417 --> 00:03:46,834
The leader, the priest they called <i>abouna</i>

70
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:52,792
Was in charge, with a desk where he wrote, with papers and books

71
00:03:53,959 --> 00:03:56,542
Interviewer: Did they perform rituals here?

72
00:03:56,542 --> 00:04:00,083
Witness: No, no rituals, just meetings and rest after prayers

73
00:04:01,417 --> 00:04:05,334
They practiced their faith, asked questions, and learned from each other

74
00:04:05,626 --> 00:04:09,250
Religious teaching, for example one priest teaching a new one

75
00:04:09,334 --> 00:04:11,959
So Father taught him, saying this is the religion

76
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:13,858
He gave him knowledge in faith
